@startuml level2_gateway
!theme plain

title Level 2: Gateway Architecture\nCentral Gateway Routing and Security

skinparam component {
    BackgroundColor Gold
    BorderColor DarkOrange
    ArrowColor DarkBlue
}

component "CGW\n(Central Gateway)" as CGW {
    portin p_can_hs1
    portin p_can_hs2
    portin p_can_ls
    portout p_can_hs1_out
    portout p_can_hs2_out
    portout p_can_ls_out

    [Message Routing Engine]
    [Message Filtering]
    [Security Gateway]
    [Diagnostic Gateway (UDS)]
    [Network Management]
    [Firewall]
}

cloud "CAN-HS #1\n500 kbps" as CAN1 {
    [Powertrain Domain]
    [Chassis Domain]
    [Safety Domain]
}

cloud "CAN-HS #2\n500 kbps" as CAN2 {
    [ADAS Domain]
    [Infotainment Domain]
}

cloud "CAN-LS\n125 kbps" as CAN3 {
    [Body Domain]
}

' Network Connections
CAN1 <--> CGW : Bidirectional\nRouting
CAN2 <--> CGW : Bidirectional\nRouting
CAN3 <--> CGW : Bidirectional\nRouting

' Routing Examples
note top of CGW
  **Gateway Routing Table**

  **CAN-HS #1 → CAN-HS #2**:
  • EMS16 (0x316) → CLU, HUD
    - Vehicle_Speed, Engine_RPM
  • ESP12 (0x200) → IVI
    - Stability_Status

  **CAN-HS #2 → CAN-LS**:
  • IVI_AmbientLight (0x400) → BCM
    - Ambient_Light_RGB, Brightness
  • IVI_Profile (0x410) → BCM
    - Profile_ID, Scenario_ID

  **CAN-HS #1 → CAN-LS**:
  • ESP12 → BCM
    - ESP_Warning (for warning light)
  • ACU11 → BCM
    - Airbag_Warning

  **CAN-LS → CAN-HS #2**:
  • BCM_LightControl (0x520) → IVI, CLU
    - Ambient_R/G/B_Actual (feedback)
    - Headlight_Status
end note

note bottom of CGW
  **Gateway Key Functions**

  **1. Message Routing**:
  • Route messages between 3 CAN networks
  • Message ID translation (if needed)
  • Priority-based forwarding

  **2. Message Filtering**:
  • Block unauthorized messages
  • Rate limiting
  • Message validation

  **3. Security**:
  • Firewall rules
  • Authentication (SecOC)
  • Intrusion detection

  **4. Diagnostics**:
  • UDS gateway (ISO 14229)
  • DoIP gateway (Diagnostics over IP)
  • DTC routing

  **5. Network Management**:
  • Sleep/wake-up control
  • Bus-off recovery
  • Error handling

  **Safety Level**: ASIL-C
  **Routing Latency**: <1ms
  **Throughput**: 1000+ msg/sec
end note

note left of CGW
  **Routing Rules Examples**

  **Rule 1: Speed Data**
  • Source: EMS16 (CAN-HS #1)
  • Destination: CLU, HUD (CAN-HS #2)
  • Signals: Vehicle_Speed, Engine_RPM
  • Priority: High

  **Rule 2: Ambient Lighting**
  • Source: IVI_AmbientLight (CAN-HS #2)
  • Destination: BCM (CAN-LS)
  • Signals: RGB, Brightness, Theme
  • Priority: Low

  **Rule 3: ADAS Warnings**
  • Source: LDWS_LKAS11 (CAN-HS #2)
  • Destination: IVI, CLU (CAN-HS #2)
  • Signals: LDW_Status, LKA_Event
  • Priority: Medium

  **Rule 4: Safety Warnings**
  • Source: ACU11, ESP12 (CAN-HS #1)
  • Destination: BCM (CAN-LS)
  • Signals: Airbag_Warning, ESP_Warning
  • Priority: High

  **Routing Performance**:
  • Total Rules: ~50 rules
  • Routing Latency: <1ms
  • Message Throughput: 1000+ msg/sec
  • CPU Load: <30%
  • Memory Usage: <10 MB

  **Security Features**:
  • Message authentication (MAC)
  • Replay attack prevention
  • Rate limiting per message ID
  • Anomaly detection
end note

@enduml
